verbose_text: Acute tissue injury, e.g., occurring as a consequence of local trauma or surgery, usually initiates local platelet aggregation, blood coagulation, closure of blood vessels, and later the classical symptoms of inflammation, that is redness, swelling, local warming, loss of function, and pain.
